text: Holmes is Not In Love with Watson  Please Stop Fan interpretations love to put Holmes and Watson in a romantic relationship  It makes sense  to a certain extent  due to the nature of their close friendship  but in my opinion  it s only that  A friendship  Of course  I m not going to stop you from  shipping  whatever you want to  but at least hear me out  Sherlock Holmes is canonically AroAce  He s some of the only representation asexual and aromantic people get  As a society  we need to stop putting so much emphasis on romantic relationships  It s harmful to people who  for whatever reason  cannot be in a romantic relationship  and it s harmful to people who can  because of the idea that one needs romance to be happy or whole    Healthy male friendships need to be accepted as they are  Media hates to portray healthy male friendships  and those that exist are quickly turned into gay romance by fans  which is fine  to a certain extent  But for the men watching  especially kids and teenagers  They are going to feel like they can t have a deep or close relationship with their friends  Which is  and I can t emphasize this enough  unhealthy   Okay  rant over  Obviously you can interpret a Holmes Watson romance if you want  But I would like you to please consider the alternatives anyway
summary: Fan interpretations love to put Holmes and Watson in a romantic relationship, but in my opinion it's only a friendship. Sherlock Holmes is canonically AroAce. He's some of the only representation asexual and aromantic people get. Media hates to portray healthy male friendships and those that exist are turned into gay romance by fans.
